page.title: 15Woodland near Ribchester
page.content: We went to Dewhurst wood and saw these trees:Holly,Hawthorn,Oak,Ash,Beech and Sycamore. There are hundreds of baby frogs and we saw a Curlew . The ground was covered with moss,roots,bracken, peat,dried leaves and a brook. We saw these flowers:Bluebells,Foxgloves, Blackberries,Rosebay,Willowherb,Speed- well,wildrose,Wildrhubarb,Tufted-vetch, Cowparsley,Goose-grass,Red-campions, Thistles,ramsons,Ivy,Nettles and moss. There was a very steep bank.We saw a skull of a Crow,we saw lots of names on a big Oak tree. It was very marshy and there was a lot of rubbish including an old bed and a lot of tins. The ground was very boggy. There were a lot of ditches,the stile was broken so we had to slide under.
